 HTML Deep Dive & CSS Introduction
Today's Focus: HTML5 Semantic Elements and CSS Basics
What I Learned: 
Semantic tags: <header>, <nav>, <main>, <section>, <article>, <footer>

CSS syntax: selectors, properties, values

Inline vs Internal vs External CSS

Basic styling: color, font-family, background-color

Practice Exercise: Create a blog layout with semantic HTML and basic styling

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <style>
        body { font-family: Arial; margin: 0; }
        header { background: #333; color: white; padding: 20px; }
        nav a { color: white; margin-right: 15px; }
        article { padding: 20px; border-bottom: 1px solid #ddd; }
        footer { background: #f1f1f1; padding: 10px; text-align: center; }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <header>
        <h1>My Tech Blog</h1>
        <nav>
            <a href="#">Home</a>
            <a href="#">About</a>
            <a href="#">Contact</a>
        </nav>
    </header>
    
    <main>
        <article>
            <h2>Day 2 of Learning CSS</h2>
            <p>Today I learned about selectors and basic styling...</p>
        </article>
    </main>
    
    <footer>
        <p>&copy; 2025 My Learning Diary</p>
    </footer>
</body>
</html>


Practice Question:
Build a recipe page with:

Semantic HTML structure

Ingredients as unordered list (styled with square bullets)

Instructions as ordered list

Different background colors for header and footer

All text in "Georgia" font


